The problem is that the media always sells that only outgoing people have good chances of finding a partner, but that's not the case. I've always been socially awkward myself, but I never had such a hard time entering into relationships, because mostly I've tried it with other socially awkward girls. And I'm by no means super handsome, just average. No muscles, a bit of belly. But what I always hear is that I'm funny and confident, even though actually I have a lot of insecurities. The problem is that we socially awkward guys tend to sabotage ourselves, thinking too highly of girls like they are some kind of unreachable goddesses who will never want to go out with a peasant like us. But if you start it establishing this kind of hierarchy, she will indeed think that you're not interesting, not worth it. You are you, and have to find someone that resonates with you, that likes you the way you are. That does not mean either that you should try to keep them below you, be abusive and that kind of $hit from "alpha influencers". You just have to establish a relation between equals, be interesting and be interested. Find cool topics to talk about, your passions and all, but definitely ask and let them talk about theirs too. It's not guaranteed on the first try, of course, you may receive a lot of no's. But all you need is 1 yes from the right person, among 7 billion people, along the average 70 years of expected life you have. It may be hard, but certainly isn't impossible.

I think you need to practice being with girls, also just as friends.Then there's the question of what your goal with the relationship is. Do you want to just have sex? Have a relationship with marriage in thought?  How you think about and treat the girl is also very important. You say you think people don't truly realize or understand how hard it is for some guys to get a girl, but to me it just sounds like self pity. Unless it's just for sex, you don't need to actively search for someone to be with. Rather than thinking about how hard it is to start a romantic relationship with a girl is, think about how you can become a better version of yourself and build some self confidence. And in case your mindset is "men vs women", just stop that, it can only worsen a relationship. Learn about women's health, the menstrual cycle for example. And show that you care and respect women, I think it could help you a lot. I hope I haven't offended you in any way, it's not my intention. I'm just speaking from personal experience and what my friends have experienced.
